<title type="html"><![CDATA[A Forgotten Sunnah: Praying Two Raka’at When Entering and Exiting Ones Home]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="https://forum.salafiri.com/viewtopic.php?t=1302&amp;p=1383#p1383"><![CDATA[
<strong><span style="font-size: 200%; line-height: normal">A Forgotten Sunnah: Praying Two Raka’at When Entering and Exiting Ones Home</span></strong><br /><br />Praying Two Raka’at when Entering and Exiting the Home Taken from Bughyatul Mutatawwi’ fi Salaatil Tatawwi’ of shaykh Muhammad Bazmool<br /><br /><strong><span style="color: #0000FF">Chapter Four: The Prayer for Entering and Exiting from the Home</span></strong><br /><br />It’s legislated for the Muslim that he prays two raka’at when entering his home and when exiting from his home.<br /><br />Abu Huriarah reported that the prophet (may the peace and blessing of Allaah be upon him said:<br /><br />“When you enter your home, therefore pray two raka’at to prevent you from entering in evil and when you exit your home; pray two raka’at to prevent you from exiting in evil.”<br /><br />Recorded by al-Bazaar.(1)<br /><br />(1) hadeeth Hasan: recorded by al-Bazaar (Kashf al-Astaar) (vol. 2 page 385) ibn Hajr also graded the hadeeth Hasan as mentioned al-Manaawee in (Fadh al-Qadeer) (vol. 1page 334) and shaykh al-Albaanee graded it’s isnaad دوج (jawwad i.e.good) in as-Silsilah As-Saheehah hadeeth number (1,323)<br /><br />Translated by: سفيد ليلخ يداهلادبع وبأ Abu Abdul-Haadee Khaleel Davis<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="https://forum.salafiri.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=56">Shehzad Sattar</a> — Thu Mar 23, 2017 1:36 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
